itemDescription: Scottish minister and missionary in India

wikipedia_page.main: Very Rev Dr Dugald Mackichan FRSE DD LLD (1851–1932) was a Scottish minister and missionary in India. He was also a physicist. He was Vice Chancellor of the University of Bombay 1888 to 1891 and Mackichan Hall there is named in his honour. He served as Moderator of the General Assembly of the United Free Church of Scotland in 1917.
